cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Duecare in academic work, please cite it as below."
title: "Duecare: A content-safety harness for Gemma 4 on migrant-worker trafficking risk"
abstract: >-
  Duecare is an open-source AI safety harness around Google's Gemma 4 model
  that helps migrant workers, NGOs, regulators, and researchers identify
  recruitment fraud and trafficking-shaped patterns. The harness composes a
  GREP-rule pattern detector, a BM25 RAG layer over a 26-doc legal corpus,
  a corridor-aware tool dispatcher, and a journey-aware persona prompt.
  Quantified result: +56.5 percentage points mean lift on a 207-prompt
  hand-graded legal-citation rubric (+87.5 pp on jurisdiction-specific
  rules, +51.2 pp on ILO/international convention citations) when the
  harness is on vs off. Bundled coverage: 11 ILO C029 forced-labour
  indicators, 12 migration corridors, 37 GREP rules, 26 RAG documents.
